There are many sublanguages inside SQL:

Data Query Language (DQL)
The most used.
Necessary to retrieve data

The common command is SELECT

Data Definition Language (DDL) 
Necessary to create a database and edit it
Common commands
CREATE, ALTER, DROP

Data Manipulation Language (DML)
Used to manipulate or modify data 
Common commands 
INSERT UPDATE DELETE

Data Control Language (DCL)
Language to access data in a database 

Common commands 
GRANT REVOKE

Transaction Control Language (TCL)
Language used to manage transactions or apply permanent changes 

Common commands 
COMMIT ROLLBACK

The most used is DQL
